{"word":"Ἰουλία","slug":"Ἰουλία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἰουλία, ας, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Rom.\">Rom.</a> name] <b>Julia<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> a Christian in Rome greeted by Paul <b><a href='B:520 16:15'>Ro 16:15</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> the name is also read in some mss. at <b><a href='B:520 16:7'>Ro 16:7</a></b> in place of <el>Ιουνιαν</el>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἰούδας\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἰούλιος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}